node.text:
This definitely got the heart rate up!! It was humbling to see firsthand the true power of a great white shark. 
And while this may look pretty action packed (which it certainly was!) it’s all in the name of science! It is so important to learn more about these apex predators and work out how we can better protect them 🦈
Hope you guys are loving ‘Crikey! It’s Shark Week’ - it’s also streaming on @discoveryplus! 

Repost #SharkWeek

node.text: Our lovely Australia Zoo crew made this beautiful video to celebrate my birthday, and it means the world to me ❤️ I am beyond honoured to continue my dad’s legacy and I hope more than anything that he would be proud. I want to thank you for all of your lovely birthday messages and thanks to all who joined us for the celebrations at Australia Zoo today. Looking forward to seeing what this next year brings, in the last year of my childhood!

node.text:
I am truly honoured to be joining The Royal Foundation of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge to help launch the Earthshot Prize. Spearheaded by Prince William, this incredible global prize will recognise and award those making a difference for the future of the planet. With many challenges facing our world, this remarkable initiative reminds us that there is hope, and that we all have the power to create significant positive change. This will be the decade of action - we can be the ones to create a brighter future; a future for all of us that call our beautiful earth home. 
@earthshotprize #EarthshotPrize

node.text: This is Australia Zoo. So much more than just a gorgeous animal sanctuary, when you visit us you’re helping to fulfil our mission for conservation globally. Through it all, we will always make sure that Dad’s vision for Australia Zoo and his amazing legacy carries on for the next 50 years and beyond. Today was amazing, opening our gates again and seeing guests for the first time in a long time. We’re back and here to stay, can’t wait to see you here!

node.text: Spent these past few days building mountain bike trails on our property in the remote hills near the Great Dividing Range. With the help of an axe, a couple shovels and a lot of work, I’m pretty stoked with how this gap turned out. It’s quite the kicker! No better feeling than shredding on a track that you’ve built with your own hands! 😆🤙 Cheers @chandlerpowell for the camera work 📷

node.text: The king of the mangroves - a massive dominant male saltwater crocodile! Mangroves are home to some of the worlds most unique species of flora and fauna (including my favourite animal 🐊). And with #WorldMangroveDay approaching, this year I have the honour of judging the Mangrove Photography Awards amongst an incredible panel of photographers. I definitely encourage you to head over to @mangrovephotographyawards and enter your shots!

This definitely got the heart rate up!! It was humbling to see firsthand the true power of a great white shark. 
And while this may look pretty action packed (which it certainly was!) it’s all in the name of science! It is so important to learn more about these apex predators and work out how we can better protect them 🦈
Hope you guys are loving ‘Crikey! It’s Shark Week’ - it’s also streaming on @discoveryplus!

node.text: Sunday July 11 at 8pm I get the honour of kicking off shark week on @discovery in the USA with ‘Crikey! It’s Shark Week’🦈 For the first leg of this epic adventure, I’ll travel to the spectacular Great Barrier Reef as a warm up before I go face to face with great white sharks at the Neptune Islands. From night diving with sharks on the hunt, to getting one-on-one with massive manta rays, it was a great way to start this expedition!
